Jay Leno:

"It was so hot in Washington, people were sweating like President Bush trying to spell Hezbollah."

"Yesterday, Condoleezza Rice went into President Bush's office and said, 'I'm off to Lebanon.' And President Bush said, 'Vacation?'"

Jay Leno:

"I don't think he understands the situation. Like today, he was asked about the movement of the Lebanese, and he said he just wishes Rosie O'Donnell well when she goes to 'The View.'"

Jay Leno:

"John Kerry said today that if he were president, the current conflict in the Middle East would not be happening. Then his wife Theresa said, 'Yes I know, dear, just take out the trash.'"

Jay Leno:

"And over the weekend, North Korean dictator Kim Jong-Il married his secretary. Again, a problem on their wedding night. Just trouble launching that missile."

Jay Leno:

"Senator Hillary Rodham Clinton made an interesting statement. She said technology is getting so intrusive, she fears that some have a computer chip implanted in their brains. She said she is against that idea. Hover, she said she wouldn't mind having a Lojack installed in Bill's ass."

Jay Leno:

"Happy birthday to Senator Bob Dole. Bob Dole turned 83 on Saturday. Happy birthday to Bob. Want to wish him the best. Bob said today -- he said today, every year is a little harder for him, thanks to Viagra."

Jay Leno:

"This Friday, 'American Idol' winner Taylor Hicks will go to the White House to meet with President Bush. That's pretty cool. Isn't it? Imagine awkward Southern guy who nobody thought could win anything sitting down, with the American idol, Taylor Hicks."

David Letterman:

"Earlier today, former President Bill Clinton campaigned for Senator Joe Lieberman. Clinton got the crowd so worked up that they had trouble sleeping through the Lieberman speech."

David Letterman:

"Over the weekend congratulations Kim Jong-Il got married. North Korean dictator. Congratulations to his new bride Marcy Schneiderman-Il."

David Letterman:

"Kim Jong-Il's honeymoon is going well, last night he successfully test fired a short range missile."

Former President Bill Clinton is "campaigning for Senator Joe Lieberman. This was great. They go to the function, and Clinton whips the crowd into a frenzy, whips the crowd into a frenzy, and then Lieberman comes out and whips them into a coma."
